Introduction

LA.G (Korean: 라지) was a South Korean instrumental electronica band under INTER BD Entertainment. Their line-up consisted of ChaeA, TA, Boni, Tanya and Dahee. They debuted on February 11, 2011 with the single album 착각하지마 (featuring Shingun) and disbanded in 2012. The band’s name derives from “LA,” which is the standard note used to tune musical instruments, while “G” stands for “gorgeous”.
